channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)

item.title: Toroidal Probabilistic Spherical Discriminant Analysis
item.description: It extends PSDA with the ability to model within and between-speaker variabilities in toroidal submanifolds of the hypersphere.

item.title: A few-shot learning approach with domain adaptation for personalized real-life stress detection in close relationships
item.description: The proposed metric learning is based on a Siamese neural network (SNN) that learns the relative difference between pairs of samples from a target user and non-target users, thus being able to address the scarcity of labelled data from the target.

item.title: Segmentation of Multiple Sclerosis Lesions across Hospitals: Learn Continually or Train from Scratch?
item.description: Segmentation of Multiple Sclerosis (MS) lesions is a challenging problem.

item.title: Domain Adaptive Object Detection for Autonomous Driving under Foggy Weather
item.description: This paper proposes a novel domain adaptive object detection framework for autonomous driving under foggy weather.

item.title: Deep Convolutional Neural Networks for Multi-Target Tracking: A Transfer Learning Approach
item.description: We represent the target states and sensor measurements as images.

item.title: COCO-DR: Combating Distribution Shifts in Zero-Shot Dense Retrieval with Contrastive and Distributionally Robust Learning
item.description: We present a new zero-shot dense retrieval (ZeroDR) method, COCO-DR, to improve the generalization ability of dense retrieval by combating the distribution shifts between source training tasks and target scenarios.

item.title: Modeling Inter-Dependence Between Time and Mark in Multivariate Temporal Point Processes
item.description: In this work, we model the conditional inter-dependence of time and mark to overcome the limitations of conditionally independent models.

item.title: Opening the Black Box of wav2vec Feature Encoder
item.description: Self-supervised models, namely, wav2vec and its variants, have shown promising results in various downstream tasks in the speech domain.

item.title: Efficient and Effective Augmentation Strategy for Adversarial Training
item.description: We first explain this contrasting behavior by viewing augmentation during training as a problem of domain generalization, and further propose Diverse Augmentation-based Joint Adversarial Training (DAJAT) to use data augmentations effectively in adversarial training.

item.title: A knowledge-driven vowel-based approach of depression classification from speech using data augmentation
item.description: Following that, the depression is classified at the global-level from a group of vowel CNN embeddings that serve as the input of another 1D CNN ("depression CNN").

item.title: Towards Complex Backgrounds: A Unified Difference-Aware Decoder for Binary Segmentation

item.title: Dictionary-Assisted Supervised Contrastive Learning
item.description: Text analysis in the social sciences often involves using specialized dictionaries to reason with abstract concepts, such as perceptions about the economy or abuse on social media.

item.title: HRTF Field: Unifying Measured HRTF Magnitude Representation with Neural Fields
item.description: In this work, we propose to use neural fields, a differentiable representation of functions through neural networks, to model HRTFs with arbitrary spatial sampling schemes.

item.title: Automatic Severity Assessment of Dysarthric speech by using Self-supervised Model with Multi-task Learning
item.description: To tackle the problem, we propose a novel automatic severity assessment method for dysarthric speech, using the self-supervised model in conjunction with multi-task learning.

item.title: Dial2vec: Self-Guided Contrastive Learning of Unsupervised Dialogue Embeddings
item.description: In this paper, we introduce the task of learning unsupervised dialogue embeddings.

item.title: Deformable Temporal Convolutional Networks for Monaural Noisy Reverberant Speech Separation
item.description: In this work deformable convolution is proposed as a solution to allow TCN models to have dynamic RFs that can adapt to various reverberation times for reverberant speech separation.

item.title: Joint Multi-Person Body Detection and Orientation Estimation via One Unified Embedding
item.description: In the paper, we propose a single-stage end-to-end trainable framework for tackling the HBOE problem with multi-persons.

item.title: FreeVC: Towards High-Quality Text-Free One-Shot Voice Conversion
item.description: Voice conversion (VC) can be achieved by first extracting source content information and target speaker information, and then reconstructing waveform with these information.

item.title: Solving Audio Inverse Problems with a Diffusion Model
item.description: This paper presents CQT-Diff, a data-driven generative audio model that can, once trained, be used for solving various different audio inverse problems in a problem-agnostic setting.

item.title: Robust Data2vec: Noise-robust Speech Representation Learning for ASR by Combining Regression and Improved Contrastive Learning
item.description: Self-supervised pre-training methods based on contrastive learning or regression tasks can utilize more unlabeled data to improve the performance of automatic speech recognition (ASR).

item.title: Fusion-based Few-Shot Morphing Attack Detection and Fingerprinting
item.description: Our technical contributions include: 1) We propose a fusion-based few-shot learning (FSL) method to learn discriminative features that can generalize to unseen morphing attack types from predefined presentation attacks; 2) The proposed FSL based on the fusion of the PRNU model and Noiseprint network is extended from binary MAD to multiclass morphing attack fingerprinting (MAF).

item.title: Exploiting modality-invariant feature for robust multimodal emotion recognition with missing modalities
item.description: Multimodal emotion recognition leverages complementary information across modalities to gain performance.

item.title: Point-Voxel Adaptive Feature Abstraction for Robust Point Cloud Classification
item.description: Specifically, the proposed framework iteratively voxelize the point cloud and extract point-voxel feature with shared local encoding and Transformer.

item.title: How well can Text-to-Image Generative Models understand Ethical Natural Language Interventions?
item.description: To this end, we introduce an Ethical NaTural Language Interventions in Text-to-Image GENeration (ENTIGEN) benchmark dataset to evaluate the change in image generations conditional on ethical interventions across three social axes -- gender, skin color, and culture.

item.title: Transformers meet Stochastic Block Models: Attention with Data-Adaptive Sparsity and Cost
item.description: The forward and backward cost are thus linear to the number of edges, which each attention head can also choose flexibly based on the input.

item.title: Improved Feature Distillation via Projector Ensemble
item.description: Motivated by the positive effect of the projector in feature distillation, we propose an ensemble of projectors to further improve the quality of student features.

item.title: Truncation Sampling as Language Model Desmoothing

item.title: Too Brittle To Touch: Comparing the Stability of Quantization and Distillation Towards Developing Lightweight Low-Resource MT Models
item.description: Leveraging shared learning through Massively Multilingual Models, state-of-the-art machine translation models are often able to adapt to the paucity of data for low-resource languages.

item.title: TASA: Deceiving Question Answering Models by Twin Answer Sentences Attack
item.description: We present Twin Answer Sentences Attack (TASA), an adversarial attack method for question answering (QA) models that produces fluent and grammatical adversarial contexts while maintaining gold answers.

item.title: Deep-MDS Framework for Recovering the 3D Shape of 2D Landmarks from a Single Image
item.description: In this paper, a low parameter deep learning framework utilizing the Non-metric Multi-Dimensional scaling (NMDS) method, is proposed to recover the 3D shape of 2D landmarks on a human face, in a single input image.

item.title: ACES: Translation Accuracy Challenge Sets for Evaluating Machine Translation Metrics
item.description: As machine translation (MT) metrics improve their correlation with human judgement every year, it is crucial to understand the limitations of such metrics at the segment level.

item.description: Moreover, we optimize the training strategy by leveraging more audio to learn MSMCRs better for low-resource languages.

item.description: Our second approach is object-based and predicts the distractor and target objects during visual search.

item.title: Rethinking the Reverse-engineering of Trojan Triggers
item.description: On average, the detection accuracy of our method is 93\%.

item.title: Leveraging Wikidata's edit history in knowledge graph refinement tasks
item.description: A number of solutions have been proposed to that end, ranging from rule-based approaches to the use of probabilistic methods, but there is an element that has not been considered yet: the edit history of the graph.

item.title: Contrastive Decoding: Open-ended Text Generation as Optimization
item.description: We propose contrastive decoding (CD), a more reliable search objective that returns the difference between likelihood under a large LM (called the expert, e. g. OPT-13b) and a small LM (called the amateur, e. g. OPT-125m).

item.title: GaitMixer: skeleton-based gait representation learning via wide-spectrum multi-axial mixer
item.description: Most existing gait recognition methods are appearance-based, which rely on the silhouettes extracted from the video data of human walking activities.

item.title: Structuring User-Generated Content on Social Media with Multimodal Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis
item.description: People post their opinions and experiences on social media, yielding rich databases of end users' sentiments.

item.title: He Said, She Said: Style Transfer for Shifting the Perspective of Dialogues
item.description: As a sample application, we demonstrate that applying perspective shifting to a dialogue summarization dataset (SAMSum) substantially improves the zero-shot performance of extractive news summarization models on this data.

item.title: A Graph Is More Than Its Nodes: Towards Structured Uncertainty-Aware Learning on Graphs
item.description: Current graph neural networks (GNNs) that tackle node classification on graphs tend to only focus on nodewise scores and are solely evaluated by nodewise metrics.

item.title: Improving abstractive summarization with energy-based re-ranking
item.description: Current abstractive summarization systems present important weaknesses which prevent their deployment in real-world applications, such as the omission of relevant information and the generation of factual inconsistencies (also known as hallucinations).

item.title: Articulation GAN: Unsupervised modeling of articulatory learning

item.title: MorphTE: Injecting Morphology in Tensorized Embeddings
item.description: In the era of deep learning, word embeddings are essential when dealing with text tasks.

item.title: Working Alliance Transformer for Psychotherapy Dialogue Classification
